  <p>Dear Mr Robinson,</p>
  
  <p>I am writing to apologise for not being present at the tutorial on Friday.</p>
  
  <p>I am terribly sorry but I&#xA0; <input id="q1" type="droptarget"/> &#xA0;unable to attend because I&#xA0; <input id="q2" type="droptarget"/> &#xA0;well enough to travel into college. I&#xA0; <input id="q3" type="droptarget"/> &#xA0;the flu virus that&#xA0; <input id="q4" type="droptarget"/> &#xA0;through college last week and I had been trying to ignore it. However, on Friday morning I&#xA0; <input id="q5" type="droptarget"/> &#xA0;with an extremely sore throat and&#xA0; <input id="q6" type="droptarget"/> &#xA0;that I had completely lost my voice. I also&#xA0; <input id="q7" type="droptarget"/> &#xA0;a high temperature and&#xA0; <input id="q8" type="droptarget"/> &#xA0;extremely weak. I&#xA0; <input id="q9" type="droptarget"/> &#xA0;to the doctor in the afternoon and she&#xA0; <input id="q10" type="droptarget"/> &#xA0;throat lozenges and aspirin. She also&#xA0; <input id="q11" type="droptarget"/> &#xA0;me to stay at home and rest and&#xA0; <input id="q12" type="droptarget"/> &#xA0;that my voice should be back in a few days.</p>
  
  <p>As the presentation is assessed I am very worried about having missed it and hope it will not affect my final result. I am feeling much better today and I was wondering if it would be possible for me to give the presentation later this week.</p>
  
  <p>Thank you for your kind attention.</p>
  
  <p>Yours sincerely,</p>
  
  <p>Mark Cross</p>
